# Cross-Platform UI Styling System

## Overview
This is the parent rule for cross-platform UI development. It coordinates focused sub-rules that each handle specific aspects of UI styling.

## Core Principles
- Mobile-first design approach (320px minimum width)
- Token-based theming system with semantic naming
- Platform-aware implementations without code duplication
- Touch-friendly interactions (44px minimum touch targets)
- Consistent cross-platform behavior with native feel

